{"type":"message","id":"fdeb11e9","parentId":"0bdb76fb","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:35:34.244Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to fix the config: the \"tools\" key under agents.defaults is not recognized. According to the guideline, tool access should be scoped under agents.defaults.subagents.tools? Actually the guideline step 6: Scope tool access with:\n\n{\n \"tools\": {\n \"subagents\": {\n \"tools\": {\n \"allow\": [\"read\", \"exec\", \"process\",\n \"write\", \"edit\", \"apply_patch\"]\n }\n }\n }\n}\n\nSo it should be under agents.defaults.tools.subagents.tools.allow? Wait they wrote:\n\n{\n \"tools\": {\n \"subagents\": {\n \"tools\": {\n \"allow\": [...]\n }\n }\n }\n}\n\nThus under agents.defaults, we need a \"tools\" object with a \"subagents\" object containing a \"tools\" object with \"allow\". So we need to adjust.\n\nAlso we need to set maxConcurrent under agents.defaults and agents.defaults.subagents? The guideline step 5: Cap concurrency with:\n\n{\n \"agents\": {\n \"defaults\": {\n \"maxConcurrent\": 4,\n \"subagents\": { \"maxConcurrent\": 8 }\n }\n }\n}\n\nThus agents.defaults.maxConcurrent and agents.defaults.subagents.maxConcurrent.\n\nWe already have agents.defaults.maxConcurrent: 4 and agents.defaults.subagents.maxConcurrent: 8? Actually we placed them directly under agents.defaults (we added \"maxConcurrent\": 4, \"subagents\": { \"maxConcurrent\": 8 }). That's correct per the guideline: agents.defaults.maxConcurrent and agents.defaults.subagents.maxConcurrent.\n\nNow we need to move the tools configuration under agents.defaults.tools.subagents.tools.allow.\n\nLet's edit openclaw.json accordingly.\n\nFirst, read current to see structure. Then edit.\n\nWe'll replace the agents.defaults section.\n\nLet's do it.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_361496ea9cfe467c8f64524d","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/openclaw.json"}}],"api":"openai-