{"type":"message","id":"35d86764","parentId":"099e70ed","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:37:50.020Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to allow the researcher agent for subagent spawning. The agents.list currently only has main. We need to add researcher to the allowed list for subagent spawning. This is likely done via the agents configuration in openclaw.json under a top-level \"agents\" with \"allowList\" or similar? Looking at the error: \"agentId is not allowed for sessions_spawn (allowed: none)\" suggests that the requester (main) has no allowed agents. We need to configure allowed agents for the main agent.\n\nWe saw earlier that there is an \"agents\" section with \"defaults\" and \"list\". Perhaps we need to add an \"allowList\" under agents for the main agent? Or maybe there is a separate setting like \"agents.allowList\". Let's check the openclaw.json structure again: we have \"agents\": { \"defaults\": {...}, \"list\": [...] }. There's no \"allowList\". However, the agents_list tool returned only main as allowed. So we need to modify the configuration to allow researcher.\n\nPerhaps we need to add an \"allow\" field under agents for the requester? Let's search for documentation: but we can't search the web? We can use web_search but maybe not needed. Let's think: The error says allowed: none. So the main agent has no allowed subagents. We need to add researcher to the allowed list for main.\n\nMaybe we need to add under agents.defaults an \"allowedSubagents\" or something. However, the guideline mentions \"Whitelist subagent spawning with allowAgents\" under an orchestrator agent. That suggests that to allow spawning, you need an agent that has subagents.allowAgents list. The orchestrator agent we created has that. So perhaps we need to spawn the orchestrator agent, which then can spawn researcher. But the user asked to create a subagent following the guideline. The guideline steps: define agent in agents.list, set defaults, whitelist with allowAgents, set cheaper model, cap concurrency, scope tool access. We have done steps 1,2,4,5,6 partially but we need to whitelist subagent spawning with allowAgents. We added orchestrator with allowAgents: [\"researcher\"]. So we should spawn orchestrator, which can then spawn researcher.\n\nBut the user said: \"i want you to create a subagent and this is the guideline:\" and they gave steps. They likely want us to create the researcher subagent (maybe via orchestrator). Let's try spawning orchestrator.\n\nWe need to check if orchestrator is allowed. agents_list only shows main. So orchestrator is not allowed either. We need to add orchestrator to the allowed list as well. Perhaps we need to add both researcher and orchestrator to agents.list and then set allowAgents on orchestrator.\n\nWe already added both to agents.list. But agents_list only shows main. Why? Possibly because the agents_list tool only returns agents that are configured for the requester session (main) and maybe there is a separate allowlist for agents that can be spawned. The agents_list tool description: \"List OpenClaw agent ids you can target with `sessions_spawn` when `runtime=\"subagent\"` (based on subagent allowlists).\" So it returns allowed agents based on subagent allowlists. Since we haven't set any allowlist for the main agent, it returns none.\n\nWe need to set subagent allowlist for the main agent. Where? Possibly under agents.defaults.subagents.allowAgents? Or under the main agent's configuration.\n\nLet's look at the openclaw.json again: we have agents.defaults with maxConcurrent and subagents.maxConcurrent. We can add an allowAgents there? The guideline step 3: Whitelist subagent spawning with allowAgents under an orchestrator agent. That suggests that the agent that wants to spawn subagents must have subagents.allowAgents. So for the main agent to spawn orchestrator, we need to add subagents.allowAgents to the main agent's configuration.\n\nThus we need to add under agents.defaults (or maybe under the specific main agent) a subagents.allowAgents list.\n\nLet's add under agents.defaults.subagents.allowAgents: [\"orchestrator\"] (or maybe [\"*\"]). But we also need to allow researcher? Actually orchestrator will spawn researcher, so main only needs to allow orchestrator.\n\nLet's edit openclaw.json to add under agents.defaults.subagents.allowAgents.\n\nWe'll also need to ensure the model for researcher is set (we already did under researcher.subagents.model). That's fine.\n\nLet's do the edit.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fcee56d455da429aa26af681","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/openclaw.json","oldText":"  \"agents\": {\n    \"defaults\": {\n      \"models\": {\n        \"nvidia/z-ai/glm5\": {\n          \"alias\": \"glm5\"\n        },\n        \"nvidia/deepseek-ai/deepseek-v3.2\": {\n          \"alias\": \"deepseek\"\n        },\n        \"nvidia/moonshotai/kimi-k2.5\": {\n          \"alias\": \"kimi\"\n        },\n        \"nvidia/mistralai/mistral-large-3-675b-instruct-2512\": {\n          \"alias\": \"mistral\"\n        },\n        \"nvidia/nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b\": {\n          \"alias\": \"nemotron\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"maxConcurrent\": 4,\n      \"subagents\": {\n        \"maxConcurrent\": 8\n      }\n    },","newText":"  \"agents\": {\n    \"defaults\": {\n      \"models\": {\n        \"nvidia/z-ai/glm5\": {\n          \"alias\": \"glm5\"\n        },\n        \"nvidia/deepseek-ai/deepseek-v3.2\": {\n          \"alias\": \"deepseek\"\n        },\n        \"nvidia/moonshotai/kimi-k2.5\": {\n          \"alias\": \"kimi\"\n        },\n        \"nvidia/mistralai/mistral-large-3-675b-instruct-2512\": {\n          \"alias\": \"mistral\"\n        },\n        \"nvidia/nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b\": {\n          \"alias\": \"nemotron\"\n        }\n      },\n      \"maxConcurrent\": 4,\n      \"subagents\": {\n        \"ma